{
  "id": 5123253146353664,
  "name": "CSS light-dark() with image values",
  "summary": "Extends the CSS light-dark() function to accept image values (url(), image-set(), none) in author stylesheets, allowing image properties like background-image, list-style-image, border-image-source, cursor, and content to automatically switch between images based on the user's preferred color scheme. Previously this was only allowed in UA stylesheets. This aligns with the CSS Color 5 spec and matches Firefox's existing implementation.",
